The error "Cannot read property 'map' of undefined" typically occurs when you try to call .map() on something that's undefined or null.

Common causes:
1. Data hasn't loaded yet (async issue)
2. API returned null/undefined
3. Wrong property name

Solution:
```javascript
// Add optional chaining and default value
const items = data?.items || [];
items.map(item => ...)

// Or conditional rendering
{items && items.map(item => ...)}
```

